						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle">WizardBones wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">I think I'm still underestimating the scanline budget.</div><br />4 sprites per scanline on 1 object/character isn't so bad... even Mega Man has frames with 5 sprites on the same scanlines due to the overlaid face. I usually limit my own characters to 4 tiles per scanline, but I try not to worry too much if I have to use 5 or even 6 on some occasional frames. Another game that got away with using a lot of sprites per scanline is Felix the Cat... not only Felix can use all sorts of vehicles and attacks that consume a lot of sprites, but the game can only display 7 sprites per scanline instead of 8, because it uses a tall column of solid black sprites on the far right of the screen to hide background scrolling glitches!</div>

